  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 11:36 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Why Today's Session is Dry + Selectivity = Profit\n\n**Task:** P3 strategy \u2014 analyze why 11h has zero trades, validate selectivity thesis\n\n**Why No Trades (11:00-11:36):**\n- BTC grinding UP: $66,843 \u2192 $66,985 (+0.2%) in 30 min\n- Bias 71% positive (25/35 readings). Crowd betting YES (correct!).\n- Our contrarian can only buy YES when bias is NEGATIVE (crowd betting NO).\n- In a steady grind-up, there's no contrarian opportunity. This is CORRECT behavior.\n- 5 readings had strong negative bias (<-25) but in windows 1-2 only. Not strong enough.\n\n**Finding \u2014 Selectivity = Profit (ALL-TIME DATA):**\n| Day Type | Trades | WR | Interpretation |\n|----------|--------|-----|----------------|\n| Low (\u22645/day) | 10 | **70%** | Selective = profitable |\n| High (>5/day) | 176 | 55% | More trades = worse quality |\n\n+15pp WR difference! Low-trade days are our BEST days. This validates:\n- V5a (min_bias=45) \u2192 fewer trades, higher quality\n- V6 cooldown (600s gap) \u2192 fewer trades, higher quality  \n- Today being dry = GOOD. Zero trades > bad trades.\n\n**Strategic insight:** A 0-trade day at RANGE 1/6 means the market is trending (even slightly). Our edge exists ONLY in chop/mean-reversion. When BTC grinds directionally, sitting out is optimal. The 12h window may differ if BTC reverses.\n\n**Next:** P4 alpha research\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 11:11 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Bug #4 Impact Analysis: Apr 2 Evening Recheck\n\n**Task:** P2 smart entry \u2014 analyze historical impact of daily loss limit bug\n\n**Finding \u2014 Apr 2 evening was loss-limit-blocked, NOT regime-blocked:**\n- My earlier report (13:42 UTC) said \"evening blocked by TREND 4/6\"\n- WRONG. Regime was MIXED 3/6 at 19h (tradeable!). Actual block was DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT.\n- Evidence: `No trade: DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT: Down $31 today (limit $25)` at 19:02-19:04\n\n**Finding \u2014 No actual missed trades on Apr 2 evening:**\n- ALL 19-20h windows had POSITIVE bias (YES_ONLY_FILTER would block anyway)\n- Zero negative bias windows in the entire Apr 2 evening session\n- So the bug didn't cost us money on Apr 2, just by luck\n\n**Finding \u2014 Bug only triggers on multi-day bot runs:**\n- Pre-Apr 1: bot restarted frequently (zombies, watchdog) \u2192 _start_balance reset often\n- Apr 2: bot ran from 09:40 through Apr 3 \u2192 28h without restart \u2192 stale _start_balance\n- With the fix, _start_balance resets at midnight automatically\n\n**Live session (11h) status:** Bias flipping -12 to +40. Ultra-flat market. No trades yet. PM prices $0.495/0.505 (tight). Waiting for stronger negative bias.\n\n**Next:** P3 strategy dev\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 11:06 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BUG #4 Fixed: Daily Loss Limit Never Resets\n\n**Task:** P1 \u2014 live session monitoring revealed CRITICAL bug blocking all trades\n\n**BUG #4: DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT never resets at midnight**\n- Bot started Apr 2 09:40 with _start_balance=$925.67\n- Apr 3 balance=$894.97 \u2192 bot thinks it's -$30.70 \"today\" > $25 limit\n- **ALL",
